column3: str

<UIForeground>F201FC</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FD</UIGlow> Quest Sync<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>
The honest alchemist needs help.
Speak with the honest alchemist.
Speak with the honest alchemist again.
Retrieve the goods from the water.
Speak with the honest alchemist.
You've come by at the perfect time, adventurer! Could you help me find someone? One of my colleagues went to receive a delivery and hasn't come back. I'm worried something might have happened...
Oh, thank you. He went to Yedlihmad, so let's start by looking around the aetheryte there.
I've been asking around about my colleague, and someone claims to have seen him setting out from port in a small boat.
Maybe he loaded the shipment onto it and headed back. In which case, we must have just missed him. I hope that's all that happened...
Well, let's head back to the Great Work. We should keep an eye on the shoreline on our way back just in case.
Hrrrngh... Mmmurghhh...
Oh no! His boat must have capsized!
I... I loaded...everything...on the boat to bring back... But something hit us, and...
I managed to swim to safety, but the cargo... I'm so sorry...
Forget the cargo! All that matters is you're all right. We'll just have to do without the sunken goods.
What will you say?
Shall I retrieve them for you?
Looks like the perfect opportunity to practice my underwater breathing technique.
What? You can do that?
Thank you... There were five articles in all... Some of them sunk...but some float.
I'm sorry to leave all of this to you, but I need to get him home before his condition worsens. We'll head back to the Great Work first, so come meet us when you're done.
You made it back! If you're worried about my colleague, he's fine. Just resting after clearing out the water in his lungs. I gave him some chai and he went right to sleep.
You managed to retrieve all the lost cargo? Incredible! These are valuable weapons imported from Vylbrand. They just need a few alchemic finishing touches before they're complete.
From here, they'll head off to the hands of the Radz–at–Han warriors to help protect the order. Thank you for everything, adventurer.
